column6: Making 35 to 37 more uniform to compromise between my Dec23 and Dec30 forecasts. My Dec23 adhere closely to the base rate. 35/36\36 My Dec30 got into more local fluctuations. 34.6/35.6\36.6
Two trading days left, Dow is at ~36,500.

SUMMARY Since we did drop below 34.5k several times since Sept I'm giving that some chance. If a dive occurs I'd expect it to center around 34,6. If a spike occurs I'd expect it to center around 36,6. If a middling occurs I'd expect it to center around 35,6. Since the trend is upward and today is 36,5 I'm favoring 36.6 moreso than 34,6 But since we seem to be in a record high moment I'm hesitant to assume we'll stay 36+

Crossed 36k so far today. Could be a tossup whether that stays that way with Omicron circulating, but I do think recent news about less severity from Omicron makes better market conditions more likely.

Outside view: - The historical delta in points from ~Dec 23 to ~Dec 31st has not been greater than 1000 since at least 2017. What little trend has been observed is a positive one i.e. the 31st has been higher measure than the 23rd of Dec. In thousands: 2017 24 to 24 2018 22 to 23 2019 28 to 28 2020 30 to 30 2021 36 to (36 expected) Summary: typically increases but no more than 1k. Guess: The measure will be 35 to 36 on Dec 31 2021 but most likely 36

There's historically been an end of year rally. That leads me to believe that the DJI will increase beyond where it is now: 35,952. That leaves two options remaining. In the recent past, there has not been an increase of over 1,000 in the last week of the year (not including January 1 2021 as that was technically the start of the new year). Coupled with Omicron, I don't think this year will break that trend. Therefore, I'm going all in on 36,000-37,000.
Sharp spike up to 36 this morning. Staying here for now, I'll probably update to favor 36 if it closes above 36 today.
35,738, hopefully won't be plus or minus 500 today. Note my future self: Please avoid doing prediction questions like this again.
Stock Market jitters will keep the DJI from topping it record, probably loose 1-2% by year end.
Geez I'm so glad the market is picking now to go up plus or minus 500 points each day. :)
Market reacted in the opposite direction to how I thought it would on the FED announcement. Seems like they had priced it in and also want to see inflation tamped down.

35,970 right now, so "Higher than 36,000.00 but lower than 37,000.00" seems a tad low at the crowd's 24%. There are 14 trading days remaining, and although each day is a random walk, there is a slightly positive expected return each day.
The MOASS is coming SOON (this week?) and how the market responds will be telling. Guessing more down than sideways.

Base rates would indicate somewhere between 0.5 to 1.0 percent growth in the month of December. Despite reaching a peak over 36,000 in early November, the DOW was just over 34,000 on the first of December. Taking into consideration the Omicron variant and its impact on the market, I would forecast only 0.5% growth in the month of December, with an ending value of 34,100-34,200 on December 31, 2021.

In my view there is some serious weakness in the market in the short term. Before omicron it was overvalued; a new variant will push it lower until there is clarity on the risk. Not the 30% drop in Mar 2020 but only needs a small correction to drop below 33,000.
Big drop today on the potential new variant. Shifting downward, though I think it's likely to come back up a ways soon.
Adjusting up on recent strong performance.
+5 in over 37k. My spreadsheet would indicate the odds of over 37k is closer to 25% or so, so I was keeping that a little lower than it should have been to be conservative.

Dow jones historically increases around 8%/year. There are around 64 days from now to 31 Dec 2021. Dow Jones increases on average 1.4% historically in a 64 days period. The current price is $35741. A 1.4% increase of it = $36242. Fed is unlikely to increase interest rate before 31 Dec, but the public perception of an interest rate hike may intensify if inflation remains the same or goes higher.

Currently 35,677 with 48 trading days remaining. While the stock market is subject to wide swings on occasion, I'm not quite sure the tails are as wide as the crowd has them, and I think the Dow landing somewhere in the 35,000-37,000 range is more like a 75% chance rather than the 52% that the crowd has it at.

Ran some numbers in a google sheet on the 74 day returns since 2000 and the above is roughly what I'm coming up with. Interestingly, I also ran it for the same period at the end of each year and returns were a lot higher. Using the last 74 days of the year is only a sample size of 21 though so it's probably not as reliable as using all of the data but it does make me wonder if there's some kind of end of the year effect that could play a role.
The secret to these questions is to price the risk correctly. If you have 0% in the top or bottom options, you aren't doing that and aren't factoring in tail risk. Let those with eyes to see, see.
I have no rational reason for this forecast other than that over time the Dow goes up more than it goes down.

It's currently 34,754. The expected return between now and the end of the year is something like 1.8%, which puts us in the 35,000-36,000 range. There is a ton of variability, however. https://www.macrotrends.net/1319/dow-jones-100-year-historical-chart
